        "created_at": "2020-06-07T17:52:08.000Z",
        "cooked": "<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/wine.asp?iWine=3277009\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2018 Domaine Marc Roy Gevrey-Chambertin La Justice</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Nuits, Gevrey-Chambertin (6/7/2020)</em><br>\nDecanted 5 hrs. Lots of good stuff going on with the nose, the full array of baking spices, succulent dark fruits, and a little Xmas tree action to boot. As to the wine itself, it seems like a hybrid of the boisterous 2015 vintage paired with the more elegantly structured 2016 - so best of both worlds. A delicious palate for sure, slightly underripe blackberries give the wine a good acidic edge, but they also have the feel of a light dusting of powdered sugar on top, giving them accessibility for early enjoyment. Light on its feet, playful even, it closing with a good thrust of pine resin and earth. No harm opening now, should be lovely in 5 to 10 years. <em><strong>(91 pts.)</strong></em>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
